<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="36" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,821,2007]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,327,1141,1167]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[336,638,1141,1166]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Schizothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="beipanensis">
<emphasis box="[336,638,1141,1166]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">Schizothorax beipanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from all congeners by the combination of the following characters: absence of horny sheath on the lower jaw; upper lip developed; lower lip developed, trilobed; postlabial groove continuous, with a minute median lobe. 
<taxonomicName box="[953,1257,1221,1246]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Schizothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="beipanensis">
<emphasis box="[953,1257,1221,1246]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">Schizothorax beipanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[314,429,1261,1286]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Schizothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="griseus">
<emphasis box="[314,429,1261,1286]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">S. griseus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence (vs. presence) of black spots on the flank, along the lateral line; distal 
<number box="[151,220,1301,1327]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" value="22.5" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="20.0">20-25</number>
% of the last unbranched dorsal-fin ray soft (vs. strong); rostral barbel not reaching (vs. reaching) the middle of the eye; eye diameter 
<number box="[546,680,1341,1367]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" value="89.3" valueMax="120.1" valueMin="58.5">58.5−120.1</number>
% length of maxillary barbel (vs. 
<number box="[1102,1221,1341,1367]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" value="63.55" valueMax="93.7" valueMin="33.4">33.4−93.7</number>
%). 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Schizothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="beipanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">Schizothorax beipanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[507,743,1381,1406]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cyprinidae" genus="Schizothorax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cypriniformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="heterophysallidos">
<emphasis box="[507,743,1381,1406]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">S. heterophysallidos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which it is distinguished, however, by the unique air bladder of the latter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="37" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,821,2007]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,351,1461,1487]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">Description.</emphasis>
Morphometric data are given in 
<tableCitation box="[736,826,1461,1487]" captionStart="TABLE 4" captionStartId="15.[151,239,151,175]" captionTargetBox="[151,1399,288,1292]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="TABLE 4. Morphometric data for Schizothorax beipanensis sp. nov." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/0FB66611FFACFF83FF0FFF3BB83A6FEF" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" tableUuid="0FB66611FFACFF83FF0FFF3BB83A6FEF">
Table 
<number box="[808,826,1461,1487]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" value="4.0">4</number>
</tableCitation>
. Body elongated, laterally compressed. Snout blunt. Dorsal surface of head descends sharply anterior to nostrils, forming an inconspicuous ethmoidal groove. Mouth inferior, horseshoe-shaped. Lips developed, lower lip fleshy, with three lobes; postlabial groove continuous, with a small median lobe of width greater than that of isthmus, surface of posterior parts of side lobes rugged (
<figureCitation box="[248,316,1621,1647]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,255,1346,1370]" captionTargetBox="[213,1382,182,1346]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[213,1382,182,1346]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Ventral view of head of: (A) Schizothorax griseus, KIZ 20060175; (B) S. nudiventris, KIZ 20050507224; (C) S. heterophysallidos, KIZ 20060038; and (D) S. beipanensis, KIZ 20060065. Scale bar = 10 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185675/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number box="[302,316,1621,1647]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
D). Only two labial lobes present in some specimens (&lt;
<quantity box="[971,1090,1621,1647]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.232" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" unit="mm" value="123.2">123.2 mm</quantity>
SL), with no obvious median lobe or posterior groove interruption, a minute crescent-shaped horny sheath present on anterior lower jaw. Two pairs of barbels: maxillary barbel equal to or longer than rostral barbel, which reaches short of mid-eye; maxillary barbel may or may not reach posterior border of eye. Scales minute, absent on thorax and abdomen before pectoral-fin tip. Lateral line straight, with 
<number box="[729,816,1781,1807]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" value="101.0" valueMax="111.0" valueMin="91.0">91−111</number>
(
<number box="[834,863,1781,1807]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" value="11.0">11</number>
*) scales; scales in transverse series from dorsalfin origin to lateral line 
<number box="[427,502,1821,1847]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" value="23.5" valueMax="27.0" valueMin="20.0">20−27</number>
(
<number box="[519,535,1821,1847]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" value="8.0">8</number>
*); scales in transverse series from pelvic-fin origin to lateral line 
<number box="[1298,1373,1821,1847]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" value="23.0" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="21.0">21−25</number>
(
<number box="[1390,1406,1821,1847]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" value="3.0">3</number>
*). Two rows of enlarged scales on each side, extending from base of vent to anal fin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,821,2007]" lastBlockId="14.[151,1437,152,418]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="37" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">
Dorsal fin with three simple and 
<number box="[603,618,1901,1927]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<number box="[638,669,1901,1927]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" value="18.0">18</number>
*) branched rays. Last simple unbranched dorsal-fin ray strong, with 
<number box="[212,286,1941,1967]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" value="16.0" valueMax="19.0" valueMin="13.0">13−19</number>
(
<number box="[304,336,1941,1967]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" value="10.0">10</number>
*) serrae along its posterior edge (
<figureCitation box="[741,813,1941,1967]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,255,1821,1845]" captionTargetBox="[177,1419,987,1785]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,932,1792]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Lateral view of the last unbranched dorsal-fin ray of: (A) Schizothorax griseus, KIZ 20060206, 141.7 mm SL, China: the Sancha River, Yangchang Town, Nayong County, Bijie, Guizhou Province; (B) S. nudiventris, KIZ 20050507224, 148.0 mm SL; China: the Lancang Jiang, Wulonglong village, Badi Town, Weixi County, Yunnan Province; (C) S. heterophysallidos, KIZ 775854, 143.8 mm SL; China: Luoping, Yunnan Province; and (D) S. beipanensis, KIZ 20060064, 157.0 mm SL; China: the Suoqiao River, Shanbanqiao Town, Pu’an County, GuiZhou Province." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185676/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">
Fig. 
<number box="[797,813,1941,1967]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
D). Dorsal-fin origin above or posterior to pelvic-fin origin. Predorsal length equal to or greater than distance from dorsal-fin origin to caudal-peduncle base. Pectoral fin with one simple and 
<number box="[501,530,152,178]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="16.0">16</number>
(
<number box="[550,562,152,178]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="1.0">1</number>
*), 
<number box="[603,632,152,178]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="17.0">17</number>
(
<number box="[651,668,152,178]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="6.0">6</number>
*), 
<number box="[705,734,152,178]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="18.0">18</number>
(
<number box="[753,770,152,178]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="7.0">7</number>
*), 
<number box="[807,836,152,178]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="19.0">19</number>
(
<number box="[855,870,152,178]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="3.0">3</number>
*) branched rays, its length 
<number box="[1199,1318,152,178]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="68.6" valueMax="80.5" valueMin="56.7">56.7−80.5</number>
% of distance between pectoral-fin origin and pelvic-fin origin. Pelvic fin with one simple and 
<number box="[1176,1190,192,218]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="8.0">8</number>
(
<number box="[1208,1225,192,218]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="2.0">2</number>
*), 
<number box="[1263,1278,192,218]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="9.0">9</number>
(
<number box="[1295,1312,192,218]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="9.0">9</number>
*), 
<number box="[1350,1379,192,218]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="10.0">10</number>
(
<number box="[1397,1413,192,218]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="6.0">6</number>
*) branched rays. Anus located immediately anterior to anal-fin origin. Anal fin with three simple and 
<number box="[1348,1363,232,258]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="5.0">5</number>
(
<number box="[1382,1413,232,258]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="18.0">18</number>
*) branched rays. Anal fin elongated, reaching caudal-fin base in mature females. Caudal fin forked, lower lobe slightly longer than upper one. Pharyngeal teeth in three rows, tooth pattern 2,3,5−5,3,2, tips of teeth hooked. Outer side of first gill arch with 
<number box="[542,617,352,378]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="16.5" valueMax="19.0" valueMin="14.0">14−19</number>
(
<number box="[635,666,352,378]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="14.0">14</number>
*) gill rakers, inner side with 
<number box="[1021,1096,352,378]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="21.5" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="18.0">18−25</number>
(
<number box="[1115,1148,352,378]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="14.0">14</number>
*). Air bladder with two chambers, length of posterior chamber twice that of anterior one.
</paragraph>
